<DOC><DOCNO> AP880520-0243 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-20-88 2254EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-HongKong-Refugees     05-20 0181</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Hong Kong-Refugees,0187</SECOND><HEAD>More Than 280 Vietnamese Refugees Sail Into Hong Kong</HEAD><DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   More than 280 Vietnamese refugees sailed intoHong Kong Friday aboard 14 boats, a government spokesman reported.   The spokesman, speaking on condition of anonymity, said therefguees were intercepted by marine police throughout the day.   He said no other details of the refugees were available.   According to the spokesman, the latest arrivals brought to 2,107the number of Vietname refugees who arrived in this British colonythis month.   At present, there are more than 12,000 Vietnamese boat people inHong Kong awaiting resettlement overseas.   More than 9,000 of them are housed in closed camps because theyarrived here after the government introduced a tough new policy in1982 to deter the refugee influx.   The others live in open camps, where they have freedom ofmovement and are allowed to take jobs in the British colony.   The Hong Kong government is currently considering whether toscrap the policy of offering Vietnamese refugees temporary asylumin the colony in order to stop the influx from Vietnam.</TEXT></DOC>